The paper deals with feature point matching for visual localization, which is a common problem in computer vision and robotics. The use of convolutional operations and hypercolumn descriptors suggests a focus on deep learning techniques, which are often used in computer vision research (cs.CV). The application of the method to outdoor scenarios and long-term localization suggests a focus on robotics and autonomous systems (cs.RO). The use of machine learning techniques for feature matching also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Finally, the use of image features suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM).
